-                    "content": "diff --git a/README.md b/README.md\nindex 2856941..3343baa 100644\n--- a/README.md\n+++ b/README.md\n@@ -1,5 +1,126 @@\n-# ygg\n+# pgg\n \n-`ygg` is a workflow tool for Claude Code and Codex projects. It scaffolds agent-specific files and manages change-driven development through `ygg/change/` with the staged flow `create → next → add → qa`.\n+pgg is a pnpm-based workspace that turns the `.codex`, `AGENTS.md`, and `poggn` workflow into a reusable CLI and dashboard product.\n \n-The current product surface is centered on workflow management, verification, archive handling, dashboard support, and optional local LLM assistance. Legacy spec-first generation commands are not part of the active workflow.\n+pgg는 `.codex`, `AGENTS.md`, `poggn` 워크플로를 재사용 가능한 CLI와 dashboard 제품으로 정리한 pnpm workspace입니다.\n+\n+## Quick Start\n+\n+### ko\n+\n+이 저장소에서 바로 동작을 확인하려면 아래 순서로 진행합니다.\n+\n+```bash\n+pnpm install\n+pnpm build\n+pnpm link --global\n+pgg init --cwd /tmp/pgg-sample --provider codex --lang ko --auto on\n+pgg dashboard --cwd /tmp/pgg-sample --snapshot-only\n+```\n+\n+repo root에서 global link 없이 직접 실행하려면 local workspace 경로 `node packages/cli/dist/index.js ...`를 사용할 수 있습니다.\n+\n+`packages/cli/README.md`는 package 내부 구조를 볼 때 참고하는 보조 문서입니다.\n+\n+### en\n+\n+To use `pgg` from this repository, build the workspace at the repo root and run `pnpm link --global` from the root package.\n+\n+Without global linking, you can still execute the local workspace entrypoint: `node packages/cli/dist/index.js ...`.\n+\n+`packages/cli/README.md` is a supporting note for the package internals.\n+\n+## Commands\n+\n+### ko\n+\n+- `pgg init`: 대상 프로젝트에 `.codex`, `AGENTS.md`, `.claude`, `poggn`, manifest를 생성하고 registry에 등록합니다.\n+- `pgg update`: generator 관리 자산을 현재 버전에 맞게 다시 동기화합니다.\n+- `pgg lang`: `ko`, `en` 전환과 관련 generated asset 반영을 수행합니다.\n+- `pgg auto`: `on`, `off` 전환과 auto mode 관련 문서 상태를 반영합니다.\n+- `pgg dashboard`: snapshot export 또는 로컬 dashboard 실행을 수행합니다.\n+\n+### en\n+\n+- `pgg init`: creates `.codex`, `AGENTS.md`, `.claude`, `poggn`, and the local manifest for a target project.\n+- `pgg update`: resynchronizes generator-managed assets to the current product shape.\n+- `pgg lang`: switches between `ko` and `en` and updates generated assets.\n+- `pgg auto`: switches workflow auto mode between `on` and `off`.\n+- `pgg dashboard`: exports a snapshot or launches the local operations dashboard.\n+\n+## Workflow\n+\n+### ko\n+\n+`pgg`는 topic을 `poggn/active/<topic>` 아래에서 관리하고 다음 순서로 진행합니다.\n+\n+1. `pgg-add`: proposal 생성\n+2. `pgg-plan`: plan, task, spec 생성\n+3. `pgg-code`: 구현과 diff 기록\n+4. `pgg-qa`: 테스트, 리뷰, archive 판정\n+\n+검증이 끝난 topic만 `poggn/archive/<topic>`으로 이동합니다.\n+\n+### en\n+\n+Topics live under `poggn/active/<topic>` and move through proposal, planning, implementation, and QA before archive.\n+\n+Only QA-passed topics move to `poggn/archive/<topic>`.\n+\n+## Project Structure\n+\n+### ko\n+\n+- `.codex/`: workflow 규칙, skill, shell helper\n+- `poggn/`: active/archive topic 문서와 상태 기록\n+- `AGENTS.md`: Codex 작업 규칙\n+- `packages/core`: generator, manifest, registry, analyzer\n+- `packages/cli`: `pgg` CLI 엔트리\n+- `apps/dashboard`: React, React Query, React Flow, Zustand 기반 운영 UI\n+\n+### en\n+\n+- `.codex/`: workflow rules, skills, and shell helpers\n+- `poggn/`: active and archived topic records\n+- `AGENTS.md`: Codex-specific working rules\n+- `packages/core`: generators, manifest IO, registry helpers, analyzers\n+- `packages/cli`: the `pgg` CLI entrypoint\n+- `apps/dashboard`: the local React operations dashboard\n+\n+## Dashboard\n+\n+### ko\n+\n+dashboard는 현재 프로젝트와 registry snapshot을 읽어 topic 상태, workflow, 언어, auto mode, dashboard 기본 포트를 보여줍니다.\n+\n+로컬 개발에서는 아래 스크립트를 사용할 수 있습니다.\n+\n+```bash\n+pnpm dev:dashboard\n+```\n+\n+또는 CLI를 통해 snapshot 생성과 함께 실행할 수 있습니다.\n+\n+```bash\n+node packages/cli/dist/index.js dashboard --cwd /path/to/project --host 127.0.0.1 --port 4173\n+```\n+\n+### en\n+\n+The dashboard reads the current project and registry snapshot to show topic health, workflow state, language, auto mode, and the saved dashboard port.\n+\n+Use `pnpm dev:dashboard` for local UI work, or run the CLI dashboard command to generate and serve project data.\n+\n+## Notes\n+\n+### ko\n+\n+- 현재 provider 구현 범위는 `codex`입니다.\n+- `README.md`는 generator가 관리하는 문서 자산입니다.\n+- project-level README 생성과 `pgg update` 직접 연동은 후속 범위입니다.\n+\n+### en\n+\n+- The current provider implementation is limited to `codex`.\n+- This `README.md` is intended to be a generator-managed document asset.\n+- Project-level README generation and direct `pgg update` wiring remain future work.\n",
+                    "title": "UPDATE packages/core/src/templates.ts",
+                    "sourcePath": "poggn/archive/pgg-status-codex-skill/implementation/diffs/002_UPDATE_packages_core_src_templates_ts.diff",
+                    "content": "diff --git a/packages/core/src/templates.ts b/packages/core/src/templates.ts\nindex 15ad170..d43e70e 100644\n--- a/packages/core/src/templates.ts\n+++ b/packages/core/src/templates.ts\n@@ -4,12 +4,13 @@ export type TemplateTeamsMode = \"on\" | \"off\";\n export type TemplateProvider = \"codex\";\n import {\n   CORE_WORKFLOW_SKILLS,\n+  GENERATED_SKILLS,\n   MANDATORY_IMPLEMENTATION_CRITERIA_EN,\n   MANDATORY_IMPLEMENTATION_CRITERIA_KO,\n   OPTIONAL_AUDIT_SKILLS,\n   WORKFLOW_FRONTMATTER_SKILLS,\n   WORKFLOW_FRONTMATTER_STAGES,\n-  type WorkflowSkillName\n+  type GeneratedSkillName\n } from \"./workflow-contract.js\";\n \n export interface TemplateInput {\n@@ -514,7 +515,7 @@ function shellRulesMd(input: TemplateInput): string {\n   ]);\n }\n \n-function skillMd(input: TemplateInput, name: WorkflowSkillName): string {\n+function skillMd(input: TemplateInput, name: GeneratedSkillName): string {\n   const english = {\n     \"pgg-add\": {\n       description:\n@@ -769,6 +770,45 @@ function skillMd(input: TemplateInput, name: WorkflowSkillName): string {\n         \"- run project verification only from a declared current-project verification contract; otherwise record `manual verification required`\",\n         \"- prefer `state/current.md` plus required refs over full document copies\"\n       ]\n+    },\n+    \"pgg-status\": {\n+      description:\n+        \"Read current active topics and explain which workflow each topic should enter next.\",\n+      body: [\n+        \"# Skill: pgg-status\",\n+        \"\",\n+        \"## Purpose\",\n+        \"\",\n+        \"Read the current project's active topics and explain each topic's current stage, progress status, next workflow, and the reason behind that recommendation.\",\n+        \"\",\n+        \"## Scope\",\n+        \"\",\n+        \"- treat this as a standalone operations skill, not a workflow stage\",\n+        \"- limit the default scope to the current project's `poggn/active/<topic>` entries\",\n+        \"- do not read `poggn/archive` unless the user explicitly expands the scope\",\n+        \"- do not execute any recommended workflow automatically\",\n+        \"\",\n+        \"## Read Order\",\n+        \"\",\n+        \"- prefer the existing shared status evaluator first, such as `pgg status` or `analyzeProjectStatus`, when it is available in the current project\",\n+        \"- fall back to topic documents only when a shared status result is unavailable or insufficient\",\n+        \"- when falling back, prioritize `state/current.md`, then use `proposal.md`, `plan.md`, `task.md`, `qa/report.md`, and artifact presence only as supporting evidence\",\n+        \"\",\n+        \"## Response Contract\",\n+        \"\",\n+        \"- answer with a short summary plus a readable topic-by-topic structure\",\n+        \"- include at least: topic, current stage, progress status, next workflow, and reason\",\n+        \"- distinguish ready, in-progress, blocked, archive-ready, or manual-check-required states when the evidence supports it\",\n+        \"- do not dump raw JSON unless the user explicitly asks for JSON output\",\n+        \"- make it clear whether the reason came from `state/current.md`, a shared status evaluator, or artifact-based fallback inference\",\n+        \"\",\n+        \"## Guardrails\",\n+        \"\",\n+        \"- stay inside the current project\",\n+        \"- do not edit topic documents while reporting status\",\n+        \"- do not invent progress when evidence is missing or contradictory\",\n+        \"- when evidence is weak, say `manual check required` or `blocked` instead of guessing\"\n+      ]\n     }\n   } as const;\n \n@@ -1026,6 +1066,45 @@ function skillMd(input: TemplateInput, name: WorkflowSkillName): string {\n         \"- 대상 프로젝트 검증은 선언된 current-project verification contract가 있을 때만 실행하고, 없으면 `manual verification required`를 기록한다\",\n         \"- 전체 문서 복사보다 `state/current.md`와 필요한 문서 ref를 우선한다.\"\n       ]\n+    },\n+    \"pgg-status\": {\n+      description:\n+        \"현재 active topic 상태를 읽고 각 topic이 다음에 어떤 워크플로우로 가야 하는지 설명한다.\",\n+      body: [\n+        \"# Skill: pgg-status\",\n+        \"\",\n+        \"## Purpose\",\n+        \"\",\n+        \"현재 프로젝트의 active topic을 읽고 각 topic의 현재 stage, 진행 상태, 다음 workflow, 판단 근거를 설명한다.\",\n+        \"\",\n+        \"## Scope\",\n+        \"\",\n+        \"- core workflow stage가 아니라 standalone 운영 skill로 취급한다\",\n+        \"- 기본 조회 범위는 현재 프로젝트의 `poggn/active/<topic>`만 사용한다\",\n+        \"- 사용자가 범위를 넓히지 않는 한 `poggn/archive`는 읽지 않는다\",\n+        \"- 추천된 workflow를 자동 실행하지 않는다\",\n+        \"\",\n+        \"## Read Order\",\n+        \"\",\n+        \"- current-project에 이미 있는 공유 status evaluator 결과, 예를 들면 `pgg status` 또는 `analyzeProjectStatus`를 먼저 사용한다\",\n+        \"- 공유 status 결과가 없거나 부족할 때만 topic 문서를 직접 읽는다\",\n+        \"- fallback에서는 `state/current.md`를 우선하고, `proposal.md`, `plan.md`, `task.md`, `qa/report.md`, artifact 존재 여부는 보조 근거로만 사용한다\",\n+        \"\",\n+        \"## Response Contract\",\n+        \"\",\n+        \"- 짧은 요약과 읽기 쉬운 topic별 구조로 답한다\",\n+        \"- 최소 포함 항목은 topic, current stage, progress status, next workflow, reason이다\",\n+        \"- 근거가 충분하면 ready, in-progress, blocked, archive-ready, manual-check-required 성격을 구분해 드러낸다\",\n+        \"- 사용자가 JSON을 명시적으로 요구하지 않으면 raw JSON만 그대로 출력하지 않는다\",\n+        \"- reason에는 `state/current.md`, 공유 status evaluator, artifact 기반 fallback 중 어떤 근거를 썼는지 드러낸다\",\n+        \"\",\n+        \"## Guardrails\",\n+        \"\",\n+        \"- current-project 범위를 벗어나지 않는다\",\n+        \"- 상태를 설명하는 동안 topic 문서를 수정하지 않는다\",\n+        \"- 근거가 없거나 충돌하면 진행 상태를 지어내지 않는다\",\n+        \"- 근거가 약하면 추측 대신 `manual check required` 또는 `blocked`로 설명한다\"\n+      ]\n     }\n   } as const;\n \n@@ -1638,6 +1717,13 @@ function dashboardKeep(): string {\n   return \"\";\n }\n \n+function generatedSkillTemplates(input: TemplateInput): GeneratedFileTemplate[] {\n+  return GENERATED_SKILLS.map((skill) => ({\n+    path: `.codex/skills/${skill}/SKILL.md`,\n+    content: skillMd(input, skill)\n+  }));\n+}\n+\n export function buildGeneratedFiles(input: TemplateInput): GeneratedFileTemplate[] {\n   return [\n     { path: \"AGENTS.md\", content: agentsMd(input) },\n@@ -1647,13 +1733,7 @@ export function buildGeneratedFiles(input: TemplateInput): GeneratedFileTemplate\n     { path: \".codex/add/IMPLEMENTATION.md\", content: implementationMd(input) },\n     { path: \".codex/add/REVIEW-RUBRIC.md\", content: reviewRubricMd(input) },\n     { path: \".codex/add/SHELL-RULES.md\", content: shellRulesMd(input) },\n-    { path: \".codex/skills/pgg-add/SKILL.md\", content: skillMd(input, \"pgg-add\") },\n-    { path: \".codex/skills/pgg-plan/SKILL.md\", content: skillMd(input, \"pgg-plan\") },\n-    { path: \".codex/skills/pgg-code/SKILL.md\", content: skillMd(input, \"pgg-code\") },\n-    { path: \".codex/skills/pgg-refactor/SKILL.md\", content: skillMd(input, \"pgg-refactor\") },\n-    { path: \".codex/skills/pgg-token/SKILL.md\", content: skillMd(input, \"pgg-token\") },\n-    { path: \".codex/skills/pgg-performance/SKILL.md\", content: skillMd(input, \"pgg-performance\") },\n-    { path: \".codex/skills/pgg-qa/SKILL.md\", content: skillMd(input, \"pgg-qa\") },\n+    ...generatedSkillTemplates(input),\n     { path: \".codex/sh/pgg-new-topic.sh\", content: newTopicSh(), executable: true },\n     { path: \".codex/sh/pgg-gate.sh\", content: gateSh(), executable: true },\n     { path: \".codex/sh/pgg-diff.sh\", content: diffSh(), executable: true },\n",
